<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="534" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,151,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="534">Comments.</emphasis>
There are five specimens supposedly studied by Ogloblin deposited in MLP, but none with an original type label. Among those, the holotype is recognizable because it the only male in that series and it was collected in the type locality (i.e., Dique Lujan); this specimen has the genitalia dissected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
